title: IPFW men's basketball set to roll with many new faces
text:
IPFW men's basketball set to roll with many new faces 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 4, 2015 Updated Oct 4, 2015 at 10:09 PM EDT 
FORT WAYNE, Ind. (21 Alive) - IPFW men;s basketball has begun practice for the 2015-16 season with the aim of another winning season and a deeper run in the Summit League Tournament. 
Key players of the last two successful seasons like Steve Forbes, Isaiah McCray, and Joe Edwards have departed, but the likes of Joe Reed and Mo Evans are back with several holdovers who will see more playing time this season and some key newcomers who are expected to contribute in a big way.
